  "text": "Luciferase reporter assays were performed as described [CITATION_1] . Briefly, the reporter plasmids were co-transfected using lipofectamine 2000 reagent (Life technology) with the miR-139 expression plasmid or miR-139 antisense oligos and the vector phRG-TK (Promega), which expresses synthetic Renilla luciferase to normalize the transfection efficiency. Luciferase activities were measured using the Dual-Luciferase Reporter Assay reagent (Promega) on a LB 960 Centro XS3 luminometer (Berthold Technologies, GmbH & Co. KG, Bad Wildbad, Germany). Each experiment was performed in triplicate, and the data represent the mean ± SD of three independent experiments.",
